# 💡 Founder Recommendation

I recommend one improvement to the workflow that will make your app much more trustworthy.

### Keep two versions of the extracted data:

**Version 1 – OCR Output**

```
Hemoglobin = 13.8
```

**Version 2 – User Confirmed**

```
Hemoglobin = 13.2
```

Why?

Imagine six months later a user says:

> "The app showed the wrong value."

You can determine whether:

* OCR made the mistake, or
* The user edited the value.

This audit trail is extremely valuable for debugging and improving your OCR over time.

